{Speech 3 Answer 29}{}{Больше этих тварей, гигантских насекомых, в округе никто не видел?}
{Speech 4}{}{My name’s Jo. Can you say Jo? No matter; you see that rectangular thing over there? That’s a\n door. Be careful not to let it hit you on the way out.}
{Speech 4 Answer 5}{}{[You don’t quite understand everything he’s saying, but you grin and turn to leave]}
{Speech 5}{}{[He seems to mull something over for a bit and then smiles and looks up at you] Maybe we can\n work out a trade after all. My name is Jo; I run this here trading post. I have some information about\n GECK. You interested?}
{Speech 5 Answer Barter}{}{[You nod your head up and down]}
{Speech 5 Answer Exit}{}{[You swing your head left to right]}
{Speech 6}{}{Well, then -- welcome to Modoc. My name’s Jo and I run this here trading post. We don’t have\n much; just a few farms, a slaughterhouse, Rose’s Bed and Breakfast, and a tannery. Just enough to\n produce goods to trade. Although that could all change with this drought.}
{Speech 6 Answer 7}{}{What can you tell me about the slaughterhouse?}
{Speech 6 Answer 8}{}{Rose’s Bed and Breakfast?}
{Speech 6 Answer 13}{}{Tell me about the trading post.}
{Speech 6 Answer 9}{}{Where is the tannery?}
{Speech 6 Answer 6}{}{Can I ask you a few more qouestions?}
{Speech 7}{}{The slaughterhouse is run by Grisham and his son Davin. It’s just east of here. He makes the\n best damn jerky this side of the Rockies.}
{Speech 7 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 7 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 8}{}{Rose’s Bed and Breakfast is on the north side of town. Travelers from all over come just to\n sample her world-famous omelets. Some say her omelets can cure people of what ails them. Frankly, I\n think that’s just a bunch of nonsense.}
{Speech 8 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 8 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 9}{}{Rose’s Bed and Breakfast is on the north side of town. Travelers from all over come just to\n sample her world-famous omelets. Some say her omelets can cure people of what ails them. Frankly, I\n think that’s just a bunch of nonsense.}
{Speech 9 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 9 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 10}{}{Like I said before, my name’s Jo and I run the trading post for Modoc. I organize trade between\n Modoc and other cities in need of food and leather goods. But with this drought, that could all come to\n an end real soon. We're getting desperate.}
{Speech 10 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 10 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 11}{}{What do you want to talk about? The slaughterhouse, Rose’s Bed and Breakfast, the tannery or the\n trading post?}
{Speech 11 Answer 18}{}{Do you have any work for me to do?}
{Speech 11 Answer 17}{}{Do you have any work for me to do?}
{Speech 11 Answer 7}{}{The slaughterhouse.}
{Speech 11 Answer 8}{}{Rose’s Bed and Breakfast.}
{Speech 11 Answer 9}{}{The tannery.}
{Speech 11 Answer 10}{}{The trading post.}
{Speech 11 Answer 12}{}{What do you have to trade?}
{Speech 11 Answer Exit}{}{Bye.}
{Speech 12}{}{Since I rely heavily on the products of the people of Modoc, I don’t have much to trade for. You\n know, with the drought and all. You still interested?}
{Speech 12 Answer Barter}{}{Let’s do some business.}
{Speech 12 Answer 11}{}{No thanks, but can I ask you some more questions?}
{Speech 12 Answer Exit}{}{No, maybe later. I have to go now.}
{Speech 13}{}{Now that’s a good question. Mostly, I just run this here trading post. But on occasion, I’m the\n sheriff, mayor, judge, and any other official you can think of.}
{Speech 13 Answer 14}{}{Wow; you must be a very popular fellow to be entrusted with all those duties.}
{Speech 13 Answer 13}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 14}{}{Nah… I just drew the short straw. It seems I was out getting some supplies and when I came back,\n I found out the townsfolk went and elected me. Seems no one else wanted the job. Except for the\n occasional argument, I really don’t have to do anything -- which suits me fine.}
{Speech 14 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 14 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 15}{}{Oh, that's our town church. The people of Modoc built it to show their faith. Lately,\n there hasn't been much to be thankful for, so nobody attends the sermons anymore.}
{Speech 15 Answer 11}{}{Can I ask you a few more questions?}
{Speech 15 Answer Exit}{}{Thank you for infromation. I got to go now.}
{Speech 16}{}{We don't want your kind around here.}
{Speech 16 Answer Exit}{}{[EXIT]}
{Speech 17}{}{I think you can't help me right now. Perhaps something will be later.}
{Speech 18}{}{Did you ever go farming? No? Whatever. I have a little business right here. Go to the farm field and help my workman with a simple task. You just need to crop the cabbage. I don't think that this will bother you much.}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit}{}{Okay, I'll be right back!}
{Speech 18 Answer Exit*}{}{I don't want to soil my hands. Goodbye!}
{Speech 19}{}{Oh, I see you have crop with you. Thank you for your work!}
{Speech 20}{}{Да. Хотелось бы. У нас возникла проблема на одной из ферм.}
{Speech 20 Answer 21}{}{Надеюсь, это не запор у брамина. Этим я заниматься не стану, это к ветеринару.\n}
{Speech 21}{}{О нет, там совсем другое. Там появилась оса…}
{Speech 21 Answer 22}{}{Что появилось? Да ты охренел что ли, мужик? Лезешь с такой ерундой!\n}
{Speech 21 Answer 22*}{}{Оса? Так возьми мухобойку. Чё за ерунду ты выдумываешь?\n}
{Speech 22}{}{Ерунда, говоришь? Но деньги , которые я плачу, вполне настоящие. Предлагаю полторы тысячи, если убьешь осу.}
{Speech 22 Answer 23}{}{Вот как? Хм. Где-то тут лажа зарыта, чую…\n\n}
{Speech 22 Answer Exit}{}{Не, бред какой-то. Пойду я.\n\n}
{Speech 23}{}{Никакой лажи. Убиваешь осу  - получаешь полторы штуки. И приз  от меня лично.}
{Speech 23 Answer 24}{}{Договорились. Показывай, где?\n\n}
{Speech 24}{}{Тут недалеко[делает отметку на карте]}
{Speech 24 Answer 25}{}{Ладно. Скоро вернусь. Приготовьте деньги.\n\n\n}
{Speech 25}{}{Да, разумеется. И чистые штаны тоже приготовлю...}
{Speech 26}{}{Как там наш уговор?}
{Speech 26 Answer Exit}{}{Выполняется. Скоро буду с отчетом.\n\n\n}
{Speech 26 Answer 28}{}{Ети! Это не оса. Это, блин, подводная лодка в степях Казахстана! Ну нахер, сами разбирайтесь!\n\n\n}
{Speech 26 Answer 27}{}{В следующий раз возьму с собой дихлофос. Блин. Всё сделано.\n\n\n}
{Speech 27}{}{Отлично, отлично. Получите денежки. Ну,  и научу тебя кое-чему. Я в торговле всю жизнь работаю…}
{Speech 27 Answer Exit}{}{Спасибо. Я ещё зайду.\n\n\n\n}
{Speech 28}{}{это тебе не гандоны из Рено в Ден возить!}
{Speech 29}{}{Мы уже не раз к тебе обращались за помощью. Помоги уж ещё разок}
{Speech 29 Answer 30}{}{Ой, ну только не оса…}
{Speech 30}{}{Не, точно не оса.}
{Speech 30 Answer 31}{}{Ладно. А что тогда?}
{Speech 31}{}{А подойди к Гришему поговори. Ему что-то нужно было, просил правильного человека найти. Что-то у него нелады со стадом.}
{Speech 31 Answer 32}{}{Достали скотоводы… Где это хренов Гришем? }
{Speech 31 Answer Exit}{}{Ой, задолбало. Пойду я отсюда лучше.}
{Speech 32}{}{На северо-восток от моего магазина.}
{Speech 32 Answer Exit}{}{Хорошо, иду…}
